---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import barnImg from '../../assets/barn.jpg';
import elevationImg from '../../assets/elevation.jpg';
import exteriorImg from '../../assets/exterior.jpg';
import floorPlanImg from '../../assets/floor_plan.jpg';
import interiorImg from '../../assets/interior.jpg';
import sectionImg from '../../assets/section.jpg';
import sitePlanImg from '../../assets/site_plan.jpg';
import usImg from '../../assets/us.jpg';
import ChevronDown from '../../components/ChevronDown.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const BRAND_COLOR = '#00008b';
---

<BaseLayout title="studiofreunde" lang="en">
	<div class="min-h-screen bg-white px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-32 xl:px-60">
		<Header
			tagline="Minimal Interventions. Enduring Spaces."
			workLabel="Work"
			contactLabel="Contact"
		/>

		<!-- HERO SECTION -->
		<section class="pt-32 md:pt-36 pb-12 md:pb-20">
			<div class="w-full">
				<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
					<div class="aspect-[3/2] overflow-hidden bg-gray-100">
						<Image
							src={usImg}
							alt="Studio Team"
							width={1200}
							height={800}
							loading="eager"
							class="w-full h-full object-cover"
						/>
					</div>
					<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between mt-3 px-1 gap-2 md:gap-0">
						<span class="text-lg tracking-widest text-sm" style={`color: ${BRAND_COLOR}`}>
							Meret, Natalia, Dora
						</span>
						<span class="text-sm tracking-widest text-gray-400">
							(from left to right)
						</span>
					</div>
					<div class="flex justify-center mt-8 md:mt-12">
						<a
							href="#work"
							class="cursor-pointer hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity animate-bounce"
						>
							<ChevronDown class="w-8 h-8" style={`color: ${BRAND_COLOR}`} />
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- WORK SECTION -->
		<section id="work" class="scroll-mt-32 md:scroll-mt-48 w-full max-w-[1920px] mx-auto">
			<!-- Project Header -->
			<div class="mb-12 md:mb-16 w-full text-center md:text-left">
				<h2 class="text-2xl tracking-tight font-medium">
					<span class="uppercase" style={`color: ${BRAND_COLOR}`}>MAIGN</span>
					<span class="uppercase ml-2 text-gray-400 block md:inline">
						Work in Progress
					</span>
				</h2>
				<p class="text-md uppercase tracking-wide mb-1 mt-2 md:mt-0" style={`color: ${BRAND_COLOR}`}>
					Renovation of a heritage-listed Bavarian farmhouse
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Main Architectural Drawing -->
			<div class="mb-12 md:mb-24 w-full bg-white">
				<Image
					src={elevationImg}
					alt="Elevation"
					width={1920}
					height={1080}
					class="w-full h-auto object-contain max-h-[80vh] mx-auto"
				/>
			</div>

			<!-- Text Block 1 -->
			<div class="mb-12 md:mb-20 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-justify md:text-left">
				<p class="text-sm leading-loose tracking-wide text-justify" style={`color: ${BRAND_COLOR}`}>
					At the edge of the forest stands an 18th-century Bavarian farmhouse – a quiet, powerful
					structure whose everyday life once naturally combined living and working under one roof. The
					heritage-listed front building housed bedrooms, dining room, and attic; the kitchen was
					divided: towards the stable side the slaughtering area, closer to the dining room the
					cooking area. This spatial logic tells of proximity, of pathways, of smells and temperatures
					– and of how precisely architecture was once anchored to use and material.
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- ROW OF 3 IMAGES -->
			<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-8 mb-12 md:mb-24 w-full md:h-64">
				<Image
					src={sectionImg}
					alt="Section"
					width={600}
					height={400}
					class="w-full h-auto md:w-auto md:h-full object-contain"
				/>
				<Image
					src={barnImg}
					alt="Barn Structure"
					width={600}
					height={400}
					class="w-full h-auto md:w-auto md:h-full object-contain"
				/>
				<Image
					src={interiorImg}
					alt="Interior View"
					width={600}
					height={400}
					class="w-full h-auto md:w-auto md:h-full object-contain"
				/>
			</div>

			<!-- Text Block 2 -->
			<div class="mb-12 md:mb-24 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-justify md:text-left">
				<p class="text-sm tracking-wide mb-4 text-justify leading-loose" style={`color: ${BRAND_COLOR}`}>
					Today, the front building is being carefully renovated and developed into a contemporary
					two-family house. Our approach: not to "transform", but to read, understand, and continue
					writing. The renovation takes vernacular construction seriously – it originates from a time
					when material knowledge and natural building materials were not optional, but necessary. In
					the layers of the existing structure lies building knowledge that becomes tangible again in
					the design process: wood that breathes; clay that buffers moisture; reed as plaster support.
					In the interior, this principle is evident in the historical bonding layer: small wooden
					pieces (stakes), nailed as supports for clay, which protects the wood from moisture
					penetration while creating a suitable base for the plaster application – a robust,
					capillary-active alternative to today's composite constructions.
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- BOTTOM TECHNICAL GRID -->
			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 w-full mb-12 md:mb-24">
				<!-- Left Quadrant -->
				<div class="w-full h-auto md:relative flex items-center justify-center">
					<Image
						src={exteriorImg}
						alt="Exterior View"
						width={800}
						height={600}
						class="w-full h-auto md:absolute md:inset-0 md:w-full md:h-full md:object-contain"
					/>
				</div>

				<!-- Right Quadrants (Stacked) -->
				<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 w-full h-full">
					<div class="w-full">
						<Image
							src={sitePlanImg}
							alt="Site Plan"
							width={800}
							height={400}
							class="w-full h-auto block"
						/>
					</div>
					<div class="w-full">
						<Image
							src={floorPlanImg}
							alt="Floor Plan"
							width={800}
							height={400}
							class="w-full h-auto block"
						/>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Text Block 3 -->
			<div class="mb-12 md:mb-24 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-justify md:text-left">
				<p class="text-sm tracking-wide mb-6 text-justify leading-loose" style={`color: ${BRAND_COLOR}`}>
					Load-bearing building fabric is secured and repaired through reconstructive measures.
					Sensitive interventions create new spatial qualities – more light, better access,
					contemporary livability – without losing the character of the house. The new is not louder
					than the old, but in harmony.
				</p>

				<p class="text-sm tracking-wide text-justify leading-loose" style={`color: ${BRAND_COLOR}`}>
					During project development, it became clear: the fabric of the stable extension is no longer
					structurally sound; the masonry crumbles at the slightest touch. This part will be
					reconceived as a second construction phase: an extension that opens the massive log house
					towards the overgrown greenery – with a light, permeable construction and direct relation to
					the outdoor space. Thus, from the ensemble emerges an expanded living space: with the past
					into the future – not as a backdrop, but as lived continuity.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<Footer
			impressumLabel="Imprint"
			impressumUrl="/en/impressum"
			copyrightText="studiofreunde. All rights reserved."
			photoCreditText="Photos"
		/>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
